      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.unJ8E4IikZUxT7x3]{Temporal Anomalies (Su)}</p>\n<p>You harness the power of a past disaster and funnel it onto the battlefield. Once per day as a full action, you deal 1d6 damage plus 1d6 additional damage per two precog levels you possess to all creatures in a 60-foot-line. The line must originate in your space, and the damage dealt is one of the following types of your choice: acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic. You can use one or more paradoxes and add their total value to the damage dealt. A creature that succeeds at a Reflex saving throw takes half damage.</p>"
